# Baseline configuration for shellcheck on the hoster bash codebase.
#
# Codes disabled here are pre-existing issues that will be cleaned up
# incrementally in dedicated commits. Each fix removes the corresponding
# entry from this file. The goal is an empty disable list.
#
# SC2086 - Double quote to prevent globbing and word splitting
# SC2068 - Double quote array expansions to avoid re-splitting
# SC2046 - Quote $(...) to prevent word splitting
# SC2034 - Variable appears unused (cross-file sourcing)
# SC2154 - Variable referenced but not assigned (cross-file sourcing)
# SC2145 - Argument mixes string and array
# SC2104 - In functions, use return instead of break
# SC2024 - sudo does not affect redirects
# SC2206 - Quote to prevent word splitting when assigning to array
# SC2181 - Check exit code directly with 'if !', not indirectly with $?
# SC2153 - Possible misspelling of variable name
# SC2129 - Consider using { cmd1; cmd2; } >> file
# SC2088 - Tilde does not expand in quotes
# SC2059 - Do not use variables in printf format string
disable=SC2086,SC2068,SC2046,SC2034,SC2154,SC2145,SC2104,SC2024,SC2206,SC2181,SC2153,SC2129,SC2088,SC2059
